trust take years to build and seconds to shatter.', 21668, 0), (109130, 'Action is the foundational key to all success. ', 981, 0), (109131, 'They will not let you have peace, they don''t want you to have anything they don''t have themselves.', 114, 0), (109132, 'Eat healthily, sleep well, breathe deeply, move harmoniously.', 21669, 0), (109133, 'Peace and love, peace and love!', 21670, 0), (109134, 'Do not be afraid to take a chance on peace, to teach peace, to live peace...Peace will be the last word of history.', 2636, 0), (109135, 'Go in the direction of where your peace is coming from.', 103, 0), (109136, 'Peace beginsWhen expectation ends.', 4786, 0), (109137, 'Enthusiasm is a supernatural serenity.', 1049, 0), (109138, 'Our heart is wide enough to embrace the world and hands are long enough to encompass the world.', 379, 0), (109139, 'Everything that has a beginning has an ending. Make your peace with that and all will be well.', 1694, 0), (109140, 'The more we practice nonviolence in our words, thoughts and actions the more peaceful will be our inner state.', 379, 0), (109141, 'Something wonderful begins to happen with the simple realization that life, like an automobile, is driven from the inside out, not the other way around. As you focus more on becoming more peaceful with where you are, rather than focusing on where you would rather be, you begin to find peace right now, in the present. Then, as you move around, try new things, and meet new people, you carry that sense of inner peace with you. It''s absolutely true that, "Wherever you go, there you are.', 3303, 0), (109142, 'If in our daily life we can smile, if we can be peaceful and happy, not only we, but everyone will profit from it. This is the most basic kind of peace work.', 394, 0), (109143, 'Peace demands the most heroic labor and the most difficult sacrifice. It demands greater heroism than war. It demands greater fidelity to the truth and a much more perfect purity of conscience.', 123, 0), (109144, 'It is better to be small, colorful, sexy, careless, and peaceful, like the flowers, than large, conservative, repressed, fearful, and aggressive, like the thunder lizards; a lesson, by the way, that the Earth has yet to learn.', 105, 0), (109145, 'We do not need guns and bombs to bring peace, we need love and compassion.', 70, 0), (109146, 'I used to think that the world was doing something to me, that the world owed me something. And that either the conservatives or the socialists or the fascists or the communists or the Christians or the Jews or the fascists were doing something to me. And when you''re a teeny-booper, that''s what you think. I''m 40 now, I don''t think that anymore—because I found out it doesn''t fucking work. I am part of them. There''s no separation. Were all one. "Give peace a chance," not "Shoot people for peace." "All you need is love." I believe it. It''s damn hard, but I absolutely believe it.', 46, 0), (109147, 'The secret of the mountain is that the mountains simply exist, as I do myself: the mountains exist simply, which I do not. The mountains have no "meaning," they are meaning; the mountains are. The sun is round. I ring with life, and the mountains ring, and when I can hear it, there is a ringing that we share. I understand all this, not in my mind but in my heart, knowing how meaningless it is to try to capture what cannot be expressed, knowing that mere words will remain when I read it all again, another day.', 1651, 0), (109148, 'Establishing lasting peace is the work of education', 21671, 0), (109149, 'Only the brave men and women can bring peace to the world, not by practicing war but by practicing nonviolence.', 379, 0), (109150, 'Discover your deep inner-self and from that place spread love in every direction.', 379, 0);
